  "updated_summary": "At a wedding ceremony, the Woman in Pink Wedding Dress, Penny, stood before the Man in Gray Suit, Leonard, under a Floral Arch, holding a Wedding Bouquet. Leonard delivered a speech about their union, to which Penny audibly reacted with \"Wow\" and laughter. After Penny delivered her vows, humorously incorporating lyrics from \"You've Got a Friend in Me,\" Leonard playfully identified the song, prompting audience laughter. On-screen text 'S09/E01 - The Matrimonial Momentum' appeared. A sudden cut, marked by a whoosh and thud, transitioned to a different setting: a cozy apartment living room. The on-screen text changed to 'S09/E02 - The Separation Oscillation'. Penny, now in a purple top, sat on a Teal Couch with a glass of wine, facing Leonard, in a gray hoodie. A Coffee Table with wine glasses and a magazine was between them, with a Kitchen Area in the background. Penny initiated a conversation, asking \"So you got something to tell me?\" Leonard admitted she might be right about him sabotaging the wedding and confessed, \"I still feel like maybe I don't deserve you.\" Penny, initially sarcastic, then expressed her own insecurity: \"sometimes I worry you're gonna wake up and leave me for someone more like you.\" They discussed their mutual fears of sabotage and losing each other, with Leonard proposing they stop being scared and \"just be...\""
be...\""
